WEBVTT

00:23.023 --> 00:24.190
[girl] The forbidden kiss.

00:28.653 --> 00:30.196
We knew that it was wrong,

00:32.490 --> 00:34.784
that he was betrothed to my sister.

00:36.828 --> 00:38.955
But if this wasn't what he wanted,

00:40.415 --> 00:42.792
then why did he come
to the field of desire?

00:44.627 --> 00:45.670
It was fated,

00:46.880 --> 00:48.673
that we should meet like this.

00:49.007 --> 00:50.008
Hey!

00:50.675 --> 00:52.385
Are we hanging out or what?

00:54.345 --> 00:56.431
I just want to finish this chapter.

00:58.058 --> 01:00.310
[dishes clattering]

01:00.393 --> 01:01.478
Oh!

01:04.272 --> 01:06.232
Should we go down and help him?

01:06.316 --> 01:09.444
He wants to do it himself,
but please come help me set the table.

01:10.236 --> 01:14.074
I hate when Dad makes Korean food,
it always tastes like butt.

01:14.157 --> 01:17.494
Regardless, whatever Dad puts
in front of you, take a bite

01:17.577 --> 01:19.621
and say, "Mm, just like Mom's," okay?

01:19.704 --> 01:21.998
I was still eating smushed peas
when Mom died.

01:22.082 --> 01:23.541
[knock at door]

01:23.625 --> 01:24.667
-Hey.
-Hey!

01:24.751 --> 01:26.169
I'm not too late, am I?

01:26.252 --> 01:29.631
I was trying to meditate,
but I ended up falling asleep.

01:31.674 --> 01:34.135
-Smells good, Dr. C.
-Hey, Josh.

01:35.053 --> 01:36.054
Lara Jean.

01:37.555 --> 01:39.641
So, uh... What you cooking?

01:42.644 --> 01:46.856
-If you just rock this back and forth...
-It's supposed to fall off the bone.

01:46.940 --> 01:50.193
Hey, Josh, come hang on to this
while I saw, would ya?

01:50.276 --> 01:54.239
Electric knife's in the kitchen,
it'll have that ready in two seconds.

01:54.322 --> 01:56.157
Looks great, Daddy. I'll be back.

01:56.241 --> 01:59.828
I can't believe we're not going
to see her until Thanksgiving.

01:59.911 --> 02:04.207
Christmas actually, Scotland's too far
to come back for Thanksgiving.

02:04.290 --> 02:07.127
Wait, are you kidding?
We're not gonna see her till Christmas!

02:07.210 --> 02:08.628
Look on the bright side,

02:08.711 --> 02:12.006
Margot won't be taking the car every day,
you can practice your driving.

02:12.090 --> 02:16.052
-I forgot I had to drive with Lara now.
-Feel free to take the bus.

02:16.136 --> 02:19.764
I can give you a ride.
I'm not disappearing, I'm next door.

02:20.348 --> 02:21.391
Or I can drive,

02:21.474 --> 02:24.394
and if we get pulled over,
we'll switch places real quick.

02:24.477 --> 02:27.063
-Top-notch idea, honey.
-What'd I miss?

02:27.147 --> 02:29.816
We were talking
about what a bad driver Lara Jean is.

02:29.899 --> 02:33.403
Yeah, we were, 
but we were also talking about airplanes,

02:33.486 --> 02:36.406
which speaking of...
I have a surprise for you.

02:36.489 --> 02:37.574
Oh...

02:38.408 --> 02:42.162
You couldn't come home for Thanksgiving,
I figured I'd bring home to you.

02:43.163 --> 02:45.748
It's a plane ticket,
I'm coming to Scotland.

02:45.832 --> 02:47.959
Look at Josh stepping up!

02:48.585 --> 02:50.545
You... You already paid for this?

02:52.005 --> 02:54.132
Yeah, I had a Google alert set for flights

02:54.215 --> 02:57.510
as soon as you decided
you wanted to go to school there.

02:58.136 --> 02:59.387
Why?

03:05.310 --> 03:07.854
Mm... Just like Mom's.

03:09.564 --> 03:12.358
[Lara Jean] I guess I should tell you
a little bit about Josh.

03:12.942 --> 03:16.070
He and Margot have been together
for the past two years,

03:16.154 --> 03:19.032
but before Margot even cared
that he existed,

03:19.407 --> 03:21.075
he was my first boyfriend.

03:21.326 --> 03:23.494
Well, space between the words...

03:24.162 --> 03:25.496
boy who was a friend.

03:26.956 --> 03:31.211
I could talk to him about anything.
We really understood one another.

03:31.294 --> 03:35.757
Okay, would you rather only drink water
for the rest of your life,

03:35.840 --> 03:39.844
or you can drink whatever you want,
but it has to have a drop of pee in it?

03:39.928 --> 03:41.221
Clear or yellow?

03:42.347 --> 03:44.098
It has to be a little yellow.

03:44.599 --> 03:48.436
I mean, pee. Definitely pee.
I can't give up Mountain Dew.

03:48.519 --> 03:51.105
Yeah, definitely. Pee's the only answer.

03:51.189 --> 03:54.275
We didn't stop being friends
when Josh and Margot got together,

03:54.359 --> 03:55.693
it was just different.

03:55.777 --> 03:57.403
Water. Definitely water.

03:58.738 --> 04:00.281
Yeah, me too.

04:01.074 --> 04:02.075
Definitely.

04:02.617 --> 04:06.746
They didn't want me to feel left out,
so they invited me everywhere...

04:07.413 --> 04:08.581
even on dates.

04:10.041 --> 04:13.294
They tried to make it
as normal as possible, but...

04:14.545 --> 04:16.464
I still felt like a third wheel.

04:18.216 --> 04:21.219
It's not that I wanted to steal
my sister's boyfriend or anything.

04:21.302 --> 04:25.473
I was super happy for Margot.
She deserves a great guy like Josh.

04:25.848 --> 04:27.850
And so I wrote him a letter.

04:27.934 --> 04:29.852
I wasn't going to send the letter,

04:29.936 --> 04:32.939
it was just for me
to understand how I was feeling.

04:33.231 --> 04:37.068
But really, I guess it was mainly
about how sometimes I imagined

04:37.151 --> 04:40.989
what it would've been like if I'd realized
how I felt about him sooner.

04:41.072 --> 04:43.199
[Margot] ...making me look
like the bad guy.

04:43.283 --> 04:46.953
-[Josh] You know how hard that was?
-You shouldn't have in front of them!

04:50.456 --> 04:53.334
My letters are my most secret possessions.

04:53.418 --> 04:54.794
There are five total:

04:54.877 --> 04:56.337
Kenny from camp;

04:56.421 --> 04:58.006
Peter from seventh grade;

04:58.089 --> 04:59.507
Lucas from Homecoming;

04:59.590 --> 05:01.634
John Ambrose from Model UN;

05:01.718 --> 05:02.719
and Josh.

05:04.721 --> 05:08.725
I write a letter when I have a crush
so intense I don't know what else to do.

05:09.309 --> 05:13.563
Rereading my letters reminds me
of how powerful my emotions can be,

05:13.646 --> 05:14.731
how all-consuming.

05:15.648 --> 05:19.902
And Margot would say I'm being dramatic,
but I think drama can be fun...

05:19.986 --> 05:21.779
-What are you doing?
-Nothing.

05:21.863 --> 05:24.449
Just as long
as nobody else knows about it.

05:28.536 --> 05:29.746
Your room's a mess.

05:42.717 --> 05:43.718
Are you okay?

05:44.510 --> 05:45.511
Yeah.

05:46.179 --> 05:47.180
Well...

05:48.014 --> 05:51.059
I don't know, I just broke up with Josh.

05:51.476 --> 05:52.477
You did what?

05:53.311 --> 05:54.520
Why?

05:56.647 --> 06:01.319
Before Mom died, she said I should never
go to college with a boyfriend.

06:02.737 --> 06:03.946
But you love him.

06:05.031 --> 06:06.032
I know.

06:08.743 --> 06:12.038
So, do you think
you might change your mind?

06:19.504 --> 06:20.505
No.

06:21.381 --> 06:22.507
No, never.

06:24.509 --> 06:26.344
When I was packing for college,

06:26.427 --> 06:29.389
I had Daddy make a box of things
to take to Goodwill.

06:29.680 --> 06:32.433
I think you should do it too,
I made you a box.

06:33.309 --> 06:37.730
I don't really think there's anything
I can part with at the moment.

06:37.814 --> 06:40.024
Lara Jean, I'm leaving tomorrow.

06:40.108 --> 06:43.027
That means
you're going to be the biggest sister.

06:43.111 --> 06:45.655
You need to set a good example
for Kitty,

06:45.738 --> 06:47.698
no gorging on chips before dinner

06:48.241 --> 06:49.283
and a clean room.

06:51.035 --> 06:53.496
Can we go back to talking
about how you're sad?

07:20.690 --> 07:23.776
[Lara Jean] Margot says
when something is no longer useful,

07:23.860 --> 07:26.904
you either donate it,
recycle it, or throw it away.

07:26.988 --> 07:30.158
I always knew she felt that way
about objects but...

07:32.452 --> 07:35.496
I didn't think she could feel that
about a person.

07:42.837 --> 07:45.339
[airport announcer]
...will depart from Gate 39.

07:46.883 --> 07:47.884
Come here.

07:57.643 --> 08:00.688
Hey, you need a magazine.
We'll be right back.

08:04.233 --> 08:05.318
You gonna be okay?

08:06.027 --> 08:09.030
Did you have to pick the furthest college
you could think of?

08:10.281 --> 08:12.325
Who am I supposed to eat lunch with?

08:12.408 --> 08:15.536
I think you should look at this
as an opportunity to branch out,

08:15.620 --> 08:16.996
-make new friends.
-No.

08:17.079 --> 08:20.791
-You never know what could happen.
-That's what I'm afraid of.

08:20.875 --> 08:23.294
If you need me, I'm a Skype call away.

08:23.628 --> 08:26.422
Until you start going to pubs
and eating haggis

08:26.506 --> 08:28.925
with your Scottish friends,
and forget about us.

08:29.008 --> 08:32.136
I can promise you I will never, ever...

08:32.512 --> 08:33.513
eat haggis.

08:33.596 --> 08:36.641
We couldn't decide,
so we got you all of them.

08:36.724 --> 08:38.226
That's Road &amp; Track,

08:38.309 --> 08:42.980
it doesn't sound that interesting, 
but if you stick with it... Come here.

08:49.278 --> 08:51.072
Alright, I gotta go.

08:55.451 --> 08:56.661
Okay.

09:03.876 --> 09:05.461
Think she'll turn around?

09:08.631 --> 09:10.007
No, that's not Margot.

09:17.139 --> 09:18.599
Can we have a dog now?

09:19.684 --> 09:21.686
No, but that's a nice try.

09:21.769 --> 09:23.771
["Chinatown" by Wild Nothing plays]

09:29.652 --> 09:32.363
♪ Innocent love ♪

09:32.446 --> 09:35.825
♪ I need to go somewhere ♪

09:35.908 --> 09:39.870
♪ I need somewhere to come down ♪

09:39.954 --> 09:43.833
♪ I need some way to make you smile ♪

09:49.338 --> 09:52.717
Lara Jean. It's only gonna take
a second. Just smile.

09:52.800 --> 09:54.635
-Cheese!
-[camera shutter snapping]

09:57.513 --> 10:00.558
Sixth grade and junior year,
can hardly believe it.

10:00.641 --> 10:02.143
Okay, you ready to go?

10:02.602 --> 10:03.728
One sec.

10:05.229 --> 10:06.230
Give me those.

10:07.398 --> 10:10.318
Okay, just drive safe. I gotta go.

10:11.319 --> 10:12.320
You look great.

10:12.987 --> 10:13.821
Alright.

10:16.907 --> 10:17.992
All set.

10:18.117 --> 10:20.411
-That's very funny.
-Very necessary.

10:22.788 --> 10:25.750
♪ One of a kind ♪

10:25.833 --> 10:29.503
♪ I need to keep you here ♪

10:29.587 --> 10:33.257
♪ I need to picture you still ♪

10:33.341 --> 10:36.510
♪ I need to...
Nothing but the foggiest day ♪

10:36.594 --> 10:39.138
-Ow! Excuse you.
-Oh, my God, Gen.

10:39.221 --> 10:41.599
I'm so sorry, I wasn't paying attention.

10:41.682 --> 10:42.767
Oh, it's you.

10:43.934 --> 10:44.935
Gen...

10:45.019 --> 10:46.103
Genevieve.

10:46.187 --> 10:49.273
We used to be best friends,
but post-middle school,

10:49.357 --> 10:53.486
for reasons having to do
with her popularity and my lack thereof,

10:53.569 --> 10:56.447
we are now decidedly not.

10:56.530 --> 10:57.615
Cute boots.

10:58.240 --> 11:00.326
Thank you so much for your service.

11:00.910 --> 11:03.454
They're vintage, but I got them on Etsy.

11:04.205 --> 11:05.790
And they're amazing!

11:05.873 --> 11:07.917
Not everybody can pull them off.

11:08.209 --> 11:09.960
Lara Jean can rock 'em!

11:10.670 --> 11:12.129
But for you, cuz, well,

11:12.213 --> 11:18.135
let's just say it's probably a good thing
you're playing it safe with those Uggs.

11:18.511 --> 11:20.471
Christine. Chris...

11:20.554 --> 11:23.891
Gen's cousin, my best friend.
My only friend, really.

11:23.974 --> 11:27.645
Know what, Chrissie? Screw you,
you know my feet are always cold.

11:27.728 --> 11:28.813
-Hey, babe.
-Oh!

11:28.896 --> 11:30.398
-Hi.
-How you doing?

11:30.481 --> 11:32.274
-I'm good. How are you?
-Good.

11:32.692 --> 11:33.943
Remember Peter,

11:34.026 --> 11:37.029
the second non-recipient
of one of my love letters?

11:37.113 --> 11:39.448
That's this Peter. Gen's Peter.

11:41.075 --> 11:44.286
Seventh grade,
my first real boy/girl party.

11:44.745 --> 11:48.749
Everyone knew that Peter and Gen, 
who at the time was still my BFF,

11:48.833 --> 11:50.501
only wanted to kiss each other.

11:50.584 --> 11:51.627
I can spin it again.

11:52.294 --> 11:53.754
You can't cheat the bottle.

12:02.346 --> 12:07.143
So I was just complimenting Lara Jean
on her government-issued boots.

12:07.727 --> 12:10.438
Come on, 
I see someone we need to say hi to.

12:10.521 --> 12:12.189
-Bye!
-What...

12:14.442 --> 12:17.069
She just stopped drinking caffeine
for some diet,

12:17.153 --> 12:18.821
I think she's in withdrawal.

12:18.904 --> 12:21.949
Are you sure she just doesn't have
a chemical imbalance?

12:23.033 --> 12:24.034
Right...

12:27.037 --> 12:29.290
Really think my boots are amazing?

12:29.373 --> 12:32.293
If you ask, it ruins the whole vibe.
Be cool.

12:32.376 --> 12:36.130
Anyway, you think I'm gonna
let my cousin talk trash about you?

12:37.715 --> 12:39.717
[school bell rings]

12:40.134 --> 12:43.053
["You're Not Good Enough"
by Blood Orange plays]

12:48.768 --> 12:51.520
♪ Deep in the play ♪

12:51.604 --> 12:54.940
♪ I see you as you are looking over ♪

12:56.734 --> 12:58.736
♪ Friends in my way ♪

12:59.528 --> 13:02.698
♪ You never could have been a good lover ♪

13:04.742 --> 13:06.744
♪ Watch what you say ♪

13:07.536 --> 13:11.040
♪ Could never mean a word
And still hurt you ♪

13:12.666 --> 13:14.418
♪ Look the other way ♪

13:15.377 --> 13:19.548
♪ Please tell me that I am wrong
So wrong ♪

13:21.467 --> 13:23.552
♪ I never was in love ♪

13:23.636 --> 13:27.723
♪ You know that you were
Never good enough ♪

13:28.891 --> 13:31.310
♪ Fall asleep right next to me ♪

13:31.393 --> 13:32.353
[carrot crunches loudly]

13:32.436 --> 13:35.606
♪ You know that you were
Never good enough ♪

13:37.399 --> 13:39.527
♪ I never was in love ♪

13:39.610 --> 13:43.697
♪ You know that you were
Never good enough ♪

13:50.663 --> 13:51.664
Hey.

13:52.414 --> 13:53.833
Um, is this seat taken?

13:54.708 --> 13:55.709
Yeah...

13:55.793 --> 13:57.169
Well, by you.

14:03.968 --> 14:04.802
I...

14:05.386 --> 14:08.806
I gotta ask...
did she tell you she was gonna do it?

14:09.974 --> 14:14.061
Because I just figure you guys
talk about everything, right? So...

14:14.937 --> 14:16.564
She didn't tell me about this.

14:20.192 --> 14:21.652
We're still cool, right?

14:22.820 --> 14:23.946
We can still talk and...

14:25.781 --> 14:27.199
you know, kick it?

14:28.617 --> 14:30.619
Ugh... Don't say "kick it."

14:33.038 --> 14:34.123
Yes, we are cool.

14:35.958 --> 14:36.959
Good.

14:38.377 --> 14:39.253
Good.

14:40.838 --> 14:42.089
Do you want a carrot?

14:44.091 --> 14:45.259
Give me a carrot.

14:48.429 --> 14:50.306
I know what you're thinking,

14:50.389 --> 14:52.600
but we really were cool.

14:53.350 --> 14:55.060
However I felt about Josh...

14:55.144 --> 14:56.353
New album.

14:56.437 --> 14:58.439
...I would never do that to Margot.

15:00.441 --> 15:03.068
The middle school cafeteria
is so ginormous.

15:03.152 --> 15:06.405
Alison wanted to sit at lunch,
but so did Brianna and Katy.

15:06.488 --> 15:09.575
I ended up rotating so everyone had time
next to me, you know?

15:09.658 --> 15:11.869
Yeah, I can totally relate.

15:20.711 --> 15:21.712
Really?

15:22.254 --> 15:23.255
Course.

15:28.469 --> 15:29.553
[boy] Whoa, whoa, whoa!

15:32.181 --> 15:34.433
Good thing I'm wearing my helmet!

15:42.775 --> 15:43.943
-Hi.
-Hi.

15:44.026 --> 15:45.402
-How you doing?
-Good.

15:45.486 --> 15:46.570
-Yeah?
-Yeah.

15:46.654 --> 15:50.366
You know people usually check behind them
before they reverse

15:50.449 --> 15:53.077
to avoid killing others,
it's a thing we do.

15:53.160 --> 15:57.957
Yeah, I'm just not completely comfortable
with using my mirrors yet, so...

15:58.040 --> 15:59.041
Yeah, clearly.

15:59.541 --> 16:02.503
Think you're gonna be able
to make it out of the parking lot?

16:02.586 --> 16:04.964
Yeah. We're fine.

16:05.631 --> 16:06.924
Really, seriously.

16:07.174 --> 16:08.968
Um, so you should just...

16:09.635 --> 16:10.636
go, seriously.

16:11.220 --> 16:14.223
Sure, whatever you say, Covey.
Hey, you're in charge.

16:21.021 --> 16:22.106
Who was that?

16:22.648 --> 16:24.066
That was Peter Kavinsky.

16:26.485 --> 16:29.738
-What are we waiting for?
-The rest of the cars to leave.

16:30.239 --> 16:31.240
Oh, my gosh.

16:32.324 --> 16:34.827
Blanche, you simply have to help me.

16:35.411 --> 16:38.497
-What do you think Margot's doing tonight?
-Crack.

16:39.123 --> 16:40.958
Kitty, why would you say that?

16:41.041 --> 16:44.712
It's how Scottish people say fun.
Like, "You're a good craic."

16:45.087 --> 16:46.088
I looked it up.

16:46.672 --> 16:48.757
It's weird not having her here, huh?

16:49.341 --> 16:51.552
It's weird not having Josh here, too.

16:52.136 --> 16:54.013
I miss his Blanche impression.

16:54.096 --> 16:55.222
How many boyfriends

16:55.305 --> 16:58.308
could a naive farmer's daughter
possibly have had?

16:59.518 --> 17:00.519
Fifty-six.

17:04.815 --> 17:05.816
Excuse me?

17:07.401 --> 17:08.402
You know,

17:08.777 --> 17:14.241
Lara Jean, if you had a boyfriend,
maybe you wouldn't have to drive at all

17:14.324 --> 17:15.993
'cause he would take us places.

17:16.076 --> 17:18.620
If that's what it takes,
I think you're stuck with me.

17:18.704 --> 17:21.790
I dunno. What about the guy
you almost killed the other day?

17:22.750 --> 17:23.876
He's dating Gen.

17:23.959 --> 17:24.960
So?

17:27.212 --> 17:28.797
It's not just that...

17:33.260 --> 17:39.767
Don't you find it kinda depressing
that it's Saturday night,

17:39.850 --> 17:43.771
and you're having a Golden Girls marathon
with your little sister?

17:43.854 --> 17:47.483
No. I love the Golden Girls,
and I love hanging out with you.

17:49.026 --> 17:50.027
Okay,

17:50.444 --> 17:53.989
I'm not telling you this
to make you feel bad,

17:54.823 --> 17:56.909
but, Lara Jean,

17:57.576 --> 18:01.830
I'm 11 and I canceled plans

18:02.331 --> 18:03.624
to be here tonight.

18:03.707 --> 18:06.502
And well, you're 16,

18:07.211 --> 18:10.297
and I don't think
you had anything else going on,

18:10.881 --> 18:11.882
am I right?

18:13.634 --> 18:15.427
That is way harsh, Kitty.

18:16.345 --> 18:17.971
The truth hurts, Lara Jean.

18:53.465 --> 18:54.842
What'd you do last night?

18:54.925 --> 18:57.177
I finished another book. It was so good.

18:57.261 --> 18:59.054
Another bodice ripper, you little perv.

18:59.138 --> 19:01.682
-I enjoy them for their camp.
-Yeah, right!

19:01.765 --> 19:05.227
-Don't worry, girl, no judgment.
-Hey! Can I talk to you?

19:05.310 --> 19:07.104
-Um, me?
-Yeah.

19:07.187 --> 19:11.733
Hey, PK, I heard my cousin dumped you
for a college student, that true?

19:12.151 --> 19:16.321
-I heard you have a tail.
-Yep, really cute. Like a little piggy.

19:16.405 --> 19:19.032
I need to talk to...
I need to talk to Lara Jean.

19:19.950 --> 19:20.951
Alone.

19:24.496 --> 19:25.497
If you need me,

19:25.581 --> 19:27.624
I'll be in the nurse's office,

19:28.375 --> 19:29.918
with a migraine,

19:30.002 --> 19:32.129
Googling Justin Trudeau shirtless.

19:32.588 --> 19:35.090
Look, I wanted to say that I really...

19:35.716 --> 19:38.385
I appreciate it,
but it's never gonna happen.

19:39.136 --> 19:40.179
I'm sorry, what?

19:40.762 --> 19:45.851
From what I remember that kiss was hot,
you know, for being in seventh grade,

19:45.934 --> 19:51.481
and I think it's really cool you think
I have golden specks in my eyes.

19:53.150 --> 19:56.695
[echoing] It's just, Gen and I are in
a really weird place right now.

19:57.863 --> 20:00.407
[distorted] I don't know
what you hoped to accomplish. Whoa!

20:03.493 --> 20:04.494
Hey, Lara Jean.

20:06.121 --> 20:07.122
Lara Jean!

20:07.706 --> 20:08.957
Lara Jean, wake up.

20:09.917 --> 20:13.045
Hello? Hey, can I get some help over here?

20:13.837 --> 20:15.464
Hey. Hey...

20:15.923 --> 20:16.924
Wake up!

20:18.383 --> 20:19.468
Are you okay?

20:20.052 --> 20:22.512
-What happened?
-You fainted.

20:23.013 --> 20:25.182
Oh... Okay.

20:26.558 --> 20:29.478
Here, give me your hand.
And the other one, too.

20:29.561 --> 20:32.689
Come on, you got this.
Here we go. And you're up.

20:32.773 --> 20:35.108
Want me to call someone,
get you some water?

20:36.151 --> 20:37.653
No, I'm okay.

20:38.362 --> 20:39.363
You sure?

20:46.286 --> 20:47.371
Oh, my God.

20:51.500 --> 20:52.501
Oh, my God!

20:53.001 --> 20:54.294
Oh... Okay. Wha...

20:56.797 --> 20:57.798
Hey!

20:58.715 --> 20:59.716
Stop that!

20:59.925 --> 21:01.635
Two more laps for you, Covey!

21:03.345 --> 21:04.972
-Thank you.
-Wait... Wha...

21:05.597 --> 21:06.598
Uh, I...

21:09.476 --> 21:10.477
Lara Jean!

21:24.324 --> 21:26.201
[boy] Hey, Lara Jean, you in there?

21:28.036 --> 21:29.037
No.

21:32.749 --> 21:34.751
["Human Right" by The Strike plays]

21:36.044 --> 21:37.212
Hi, Lucas.

21:37.921 --> 21:38.964
Hey, Lara Jean.

21:44.344 --> 21:46.763
That ascot looks really cool on you.

21:46.847 --> 21:48.307
Oh, yeah. Thanks.

21:49.099 --> 21:50.684
It's actually a cravat.

21:53.228 --> 21:55.147
I really like your braid crown.

21:55.480 --> 21:57.190
Oh, cool. Cool.

21:57.316 --> 21:58.817
My sister did it for me.

21:59.609 --> 22:01.028
I...  It's dope.

22:04.823 --> 22:06.408
Do you maybe wanna dance?

22:08.618 --> 22:11.663
Oh, my God. I never thought you'd ask!

22:30.098 --> 22:32.267
Look, I didn't mean to barge in on you.

22:32.351 --> 22:35.937
I saw you run in here and I wanted
to make sure you're OK, and, uh...

22:36.938 --> 22:39.983
thought you might want that back.
It seemed a little personal.

22:40.650 --> 22:42.694
Lucas, I wrote this years ago.

22:42.778 --> 22:44.571
Freshman homecoming, right?

22:48.325 --> 22:50.660
I had a lot of fun that night, too.

22:52.746 --> 22:56.833
But I feel like I should tell you, though,
you know I'm gay, right?

22:56.917 --> 22:57.959
I did not.

22:58.960 --> 23:02.506
Yes. Of course, yes. I... I did. I did.

23:03.090 --> 23:07.052
But don't like tell anyone, though.
I'm out and I'm not ashamed.

23:07.135 --> 23:08.553
You know, my mom knows.

23:08.845 --> 23:11.139
My dad kinda knows.

23:12.140 --> 23:13.350
It's just...

23:14.434 --> 23:16.561
-High school.
-High school. Yeah.

23:27.697 --> 23:28.865
Hey, sweetheart.

23:28.949 --> 23:29.950
Hi, Dad.

23:30.033 --> 23:31.076
All good?

23:33.662 --> 23:38.083
Have you seen a green box? It has fabric
on top, it's round, there's a bow on it.

23:38.166 --> 23:41.670
Wow. No "hi, Dad,"
no "why are you home early?"

23:41.753 --> 23:45.048
Maybe because your patient delivered
in under six hours,

23:45.132 --> 23:48.301
you brought a new life into the world,
and you're home to...

23:48.385 --> 23:52.472
I really need to know.
Mom gave it to me. It's very important.

23:52.556 --> 23:55.851
I don't know. Maybe it went out
with the Goodwill boxes.

23:58.019 --> 23:59.187
The Goodwill boxes?

24:03.817 --> 24:05.527
No, no.

24:05.610 --> 24:07.446
Hey, you got some mail.

24:14.161 --> 24:15.579
This is all your fault!

24:16.746 --> 24:17.956
I hate everyone!

24:20.333 --> 24:21.460
What's her problem?

24:21.835 --> 24:22.919
Moon day?

24:23.211 --> 24:24.337
Moon day?

24:24.588 --> 24:27.799
Menstruation is science,
nothing to do with the moon.

24:28.008 --> 24:30.260
Says you, doctor man!

24:30.385 --> 24:32.846
But the Goddess within says
it's a sacred rhythm

24:32.929 --> 24:35.557
that represents the deepest celebration
of womanhood.

24:37.058 --> 24:40.645
The letters are out. They're out.
There's nothing you can do about it.

24:40.729 --> 24:44.107
Silver lining,
Kenny's letter was addressed to camp,

24:44.191 --> 24:48.528
so at least he'll never find out how hard
you were crushing after Chubby Bunny.

24:48.612 --> 24:50.071
You really oughta relax.

24:51.198 --> 24:52.574
I know you love me.

24:53.158 --> 24:54.868
Loved, past tense.

24:54.951 --> 24:56.244
You're Margot's.

24:56.786 --> 24:59.164
Dear Josh, I lie awake at night

24:59.247 --> 25:01.708
and imagine running my fingers
through your hair.

25:02.334 --> 25:04.586
-Feeling your strong arms aro--
-Shut up!

25:05.754 --> 25:06.796
You're not real.

25:08.715 --> 25:10.717
-I'm more real to you than he is.
-[doorbell rings]

25:11.259 --> 25:12.594
What are you doing?

25:14.804 --> 25:15.805
Nothing.

25:17.265 --> 25:19.309
Lara Jean, Josh is here.

25:20.018 --> 25:21.019
You never saw me!

25:29.361 --> 25:30.362
Ow!

25:30.820 --> 25:33.281
Ow, ow, ow. Ow!

26:01.518 --> 26:02.602
Hey, Covey.

26:06.940 --> 26:09.484
Oh... Anything for your friend?

26:09.568 --> 26:10.569
He's not with me.

26:10.652 --> 26:12.737
I'd like a chocolate shake. Thanks.

26:12.821 --> 26:13.822
-Sure.
-Yeah.

26:16.616 --> 26:18.034
So what you doing here?

26:18.118 --> 26:21.496
I'm just here to take down
one of those chocolate shakes.

26:21.580 --> 26:22.497
Cool.

26:22.998 --> 26:27.544
Actually, I stopped at your house,
your sister said you'd probably be here.

26:27.627 --> 26:30.380
Look, I just wanna be super clear.

26:30.964 --> 26:31.965
-Okay.
-Okay?

26:32.048 --> 26:34.467
I'm flattered, I am, but...

26:35.385 --> 26:37.554
Gen and I, like, just broke up so...

26:37.637 --> 26:39.306
Are you trying to reject me?

26:39.389 --> 26:42.767
Yeah, it didn't really seem like it took
the first time.

26:42.851 --> 26:45.312
Peter Kavinsky,
I'm not trying to date you.

26:45.395 --> 26:49.858
Your mouth is saying something,
but your mouth said something different.

26:50.442 --> 26:51.276
What?

26:53.028 --> 26:55.238
Thank you, uh... Joan.

26:59.618 --> 27:03.997
Okay, um... So here's the thing,
I don't actually like you.

27:04.080 --> 27:06.499
I just had to make it look
like I liked you

27:06.583 --> 27:08.918
so someone else wouldn't think
I liked them.

27:09.002 --> 27:11.504
Oh, okay. Okay, who?

27:11.588 --> 27:12.631
-What?
-Who?

27:12.714 --> 27:15.216
You gotta tell me
who this mystery stud is,

27:15.300 --> 27:19.596
otherwise I'm gonna go on believing
you have a secret tattoo with my face on.

27:19.679 --> 27:20.680
No.

27:20.764 --> 27:23.683
Should I tell the school
that you wrote me a love letter?

27:23.767 --> 27:25.477
Okay, okay. Fine. Fine. Um...

27:26.186 --> 27:27.437
It's Josh Sanderson.

27:27.520 --> 27:31.316
Wait, hold on, Sanderson?
Doesn't that guy date your sister?

27:31.441 --> 27:32.275
Yeah...

27:33.026 --> 27:37.072
Well, he dated my sister,
in the past tense.

27:37.155 --> 27:40.742
He also got a letter, so you can see
how awkward and complicated

27:40.825 --> 27:43.953
-that's gonna get if he thinks I like him.
-Hold on. Stop.

27:44.037 --> 27:46.289
I'm not the only guy that got a letter?

27:47.207 --> 27:51.294
Wow, you really think you're special,
then you find out she wrote two guys.

27:51.378 --> 27:54.172
I wrote five,
so don't go feeling too special.

27:54.255 --> 27:56.466
-You wrote five love letters?
-Yeah.

27:56.549 --> 27:58.426
Damn, Covey, you're a player.

27:58.510 --> 28:00.720
Who else did you write letters to?

28:00.804 --> 28:03.598
-If I tell you will you leave me alone?
-Maybe.

28:04.641 --> 28:05.725
Okay, Lucas James.

28:05.809 --> 28:06.976
He's... He's gay.

28:07.060 --> 28:08.812
-You don't know that.
-Everyone knows.

28:09.896 --> 28:11.815
-Who else?
-Um...

28:11.898 --> 28:16.111
Someone from camp and someone
I went to Model UN with in fifth grade.

28:17.195 --> 28:19.030
So, are we good here?

28:19.114 --> 28:21.533
Um... Yeah. No, yeah, we're good.

28:22.325 --> 28:23.493
Okay, great.

28:23.576 --> 28:24.577
Wait, wait, wait.

28:24.661 --> 28:25.662
It's just...

28:26.037 --> 28:29.040
That sparkly bike out front,
is that your ride?

28:30.458 --> 28:31.459
Yeah.

28:38.049 --> 28:39.384
Thanks for driving me.

28:39.467 --> 28:40.552
Yeah, sure.

28:41.219 --> 28:45.306
-Sorry for the whole jumping you thing.
-Coulda been worse, right?

28:47.308 --> 28:49.519
What are you gonna say to Sanderson?

28:50.019 --> 28:53.857
-I guess the truth.
-Yeah, but, you know...

28:53.940 --> 28:56.943
What is the truth? 
Do you like him, do you not like him?

28:57.777 --> 28:59.946
It's not your problem, Peter.

29:11.207 --> 29:12.959
Hey, hold on.

29:15.712 --> 29:17.672
What if you didn't tell him?

29:18.840 --> 29:19.716
What?

29:19.799 --> 29:23.428
What if we let people think
we were actually together?

29:23.511 --> 29:24.929
Just for a little while.

29:25.013 --> 29:28.057
And not just Sanderson. I mean everybody.

29:28.141 --> 29:30.185
Why would you want that?

29:30.268 --> 29:33.354
For starters, when Gen heard 
you kissed me, she went nuts,

29:33.438 --> 29:37.484
and if she thinks you and I are a thing,
she'll want to get back together.

29:37.567 --> 29:40.028
Oh, so you wanna use me as your pawn?

29:40.111 --> 29:45.408
Ah, well, see... Technically, you used me
as your pawn first when you jumped me.

29:48.912 --> 29:52.499
You don't have to give me an answer now,
just think about it, okay?

29:52.582 --> 29:54.626
Yep. Don't hold your breath.

30:04.427 --> 30:07.472
Yo, Sanderson, yeah?

30:08.264 --> 30:09.682
Taking Lara Jean home?

30:10.517 --> 30:11.518
Looks like it.

30:17.232 --> 30:20.276
Hey, how long you two been hanging out?

30:21.236 --> 30:22.237
Uh...

30:23.112 --> 30:24.113
Not long.

30:38.086 --> 30:39.087
[phone beeps]

30:42.257 --> 30:44.050
-[Josh] Will you call me?
-[Lara Jean] Stop.

30:44.133 --> 30:47.303
There's so much I wanna talk about,
music I wanna share,

30:47.387 --> 30:49.180
tattoos I wanna get with you.

30:49.264 --> 30:51.099
Stop. Josh, this cannot happen.

30:51.182 --> 30:52.725
We'd be so great together.

30:52.809 --> 30:54.519
Oh, my God. Shut it.

30:59.023 --> 31:00.567
It's a cool trick, right?

31:01.609 --> 31:03.319
You wanna see me do it again?

31:06.823 --> 31:07.949
Oh, my God.

31:16.332 --> 31:18.001
Hey, Kavinsky!

31:25.008 --> 31:25.842
What?

31:26.426 --> 31:27.510
Let's do this.

31:40.648 --> 31:41.858
I'm going to trig.

31:43.651 --> 31:45.528
-Have a nice day.
-Yeah.

31:45.612 --> 31:46.696
Carry on.

31:47.405 --> 31:48.448
As you were.

31:48.531 --> 31:51.826
So, first things first,
we need to have a contract

31:51.910 --> 31:54.412
so we're on the same page
about the rules.

31:54.746 --> 31:59.375
You got rules? Come on, you really know
how to zap the fun out of a situation.

31:59.459 --> 32:03.129
It's important to know
where you stand on certain issues.

32:03.212 --> 32:04.213
Okay, like what?

32:05.006 --> 32:07.342
For example,
I don't want you to kiss me anymore.

32:08.551 --> 32:11.012
You crazy? Who's gonna believe
we're in a relationship

32:11.095 --> 32:12.513
if I'm not allowed to kiss you?

32:12.597 --> 32:15.183
You may be the James Dean
of this kind of stuff

32:15.266 --> 32:17.101
but I've never had a boyfriend.

32:17.602 --> 32:20.647
You have the references
of an 80-year-old woman.

32:21.648 --> 32:23.024
What does that matter?

32:23.107 --> 32:26.319
It matters because 
I don't want all my firsts to be fake.

32:26.402 --> 32:30.073
If I'm making out with someone,
I'm gonna do it for real.

32:30.156 --> 32:31.741
But you kissed me first.

32:34.452 --> 32:35.870
This is non-negotiable.

32:37.872 --> 32:38.873
Fine.

32:41.334 --> 32:45.588
We need to figure something out
because people are gonna get suspicious

32:45.672 --> 32:47.715
if I'm not allowed to touch you.

32:47.799 --> 32:53.096
Okay, you have a point. How about this?
You can put your hand in my back pocket.

32:53.179 --> 32:56.599
Hand in your back pocket?
What the hell is that?

32:56.975 --> 32:58.059
Sixteen Candles?

32:58.977 --> 33:00.478
It's the opening image.

33:01.646 --> 33:02.939
It's a couples thing.

33:03.022 --> 33:05.358
Yeah, maybe in the '70s.

33:05.441 --> 33:07.443
Sixteen Candles was the '80s.
John Hughes?

33:08.528 --> 33:09.529
-Nothing?
-Mm.

33:09.612 --> 33:10.863
Okay...

33:11.114 --> 33:12.115
Two more rules.

33:12.198 --> 33:15.451
You have to watch Sixteen Candles with me
because it's a classic,

33:15.535 --> 33:19.539
and we can never tell anyone
this relationship is fake,

33:19.622 --> 33:22.166
because it would be too humiliating
for both of us.

33:22.250 --> 33:24.377
Duh, first rule of Fight Club.

33:24.460 --> 33:25.294
What?

33:25.378 --> 33:28.548
Are you serious?
You've never seen Fight Club?

33:29.215 --> 33:32.218
Oh, my God!
Okay, write it down. Double feature.

33:32.301 --> 33:36.222
After we watch the Candles movie,
we are watching Fight Club.

33:36.305 --> 33:37.432
Fight Club...

33:38.141 --> 33:39.851
Sixteen Candles...

33:40.727 --> 33:41.894
No snitching.

33:43.730 --> 33:44.856
Anything else?

33:49.444 --> 33:50.737
I could...

33:51.362 --> 33:52.822
I could write you notes,

33:53.865 --> 33:54.949
every day.

33:57.243 --> 33:58.244
You'd do that?

33:58.327 --> 33:59.328
Sure.

34:01.205 --> 34:04.876
Gen was always on me
to write her them. I never did,

34:04.959 --> 34:07.003
so if I start sending them to you,

34:07.503 --> 34:09.464
she'll be pissed, it'll be good.

34:11.340 --> 34:12.800
How romantic.

34:12.884 --> 34:16.846
Also, you have to come with me
to my lacrosse games and parties.

34:16.929 --> 34:19.974
You have to pick up my sister and I
and drive us to school.

34:20.058 --> 34:21.059
Okay.

34:23.311 --> 34:25.438
But you're coming on the ski trip.

34:27.690 --> 34:30.401
Whoa...
The Adler High ski trip was infamous

34:30.485 --> 34:34.280
for being the location where
more students lost their virginity

34:34.363 --> 34:36.491
than Senior Week and Prom combined.

34:37.283 --> 34:38.409
I have never been.

34:39.243 --> 34:40.286
Obviously.

34:40.369 --> 34:41.370
Um...

34:42.038 --> 34:46.167
That's three months away. Do you think
we're still gonna be doing this?

34:46.793 --> 34:48.836
Let's call it a contingency.

34:49.420 --> 34:53.299
No one in their right mind is gonna let
their boyfriend go without them,

34:53.382 --> 34:56.928
so if we are still doing this
by the time it comes around,

34:58.137 --> 34:59.263
you have to go with me.

35:00.139 --> 35:03.351
I'm certain that by the time
the ski trip comes around,

35:03.434 --> 35:08.022
Peter and I will be ancient history,
and that is the only reason I say...

35:08.106 --> 35:09.774
Okay. Deal.

35:25.957 --> 35:28.251
Come on, Kitty. We're gonna be late.

35:28.334 --> 35:32.088
I hate taking the bus.
Can you please man up and start driving?

35:32.171 --> 35:33.297
Actually...

35:33.381 --> 35:34.465
[car horn honks]

35:38.970 --> 35:41.055
Hey. Y'all ready?

35:41.597 --> 35:43.141
Oh, hell, yes!

35:48.104 --> 35:49.856
Hey, little LJ, what is that?

35:50.231 --> 35:51.816
A Korean yogurt smoothie.

35:51.899 --> 35:55.194
And my name, thanks for asking,
is Katherine Song Covey.

35:55.278 --> 35:58.364
Kitty to my friends.
You can call me Katherine.

35:58.447 --> 36:00.700
Yes, ma'am. She's feisty!

36:01.534 --> 36:03.244
Kitty, put on your seat belt.

36:04.620 --> 36:07.165
So how exactly
do you know my sister again?

36:08.583 --> 36:10.251
I guess I'm her boyfriend.

36:11.878 --> 36:13.171
Can I have some of that?

36:13.880 --> 36:14.881
Sure.

36:18.926 --> 36:21.721
Oh, wow. That is really good.

36:21.804 --> 36:23.764
Hey, what do I have to do

36:23.848 --> 36:26.309
to get you to bring me
one of these tomorrow?

36:26.392 --> 36:27.810
You're driving us again?

36:27.894 --> 36:28.936
Yeah, of course.

36:29.020 --> 36:30.730
Okay, you can call me Kitty!

36:32.481 --> 36:33.399
Progress!

36:43.534 --> 36:48.206
I was used to being invisible,
but now, people were looking at me,

36:48.831 --> 36:50.041
talking about me.

36:57.089 --> 36:58.216
What are you doing?

36:58.299 --> 36:59.300
This is for you.

37:05.848 --> 37:07.016
Good job.

37:08.559 --> 37:10.228
I'll see you in a bit, okay?

37:14.523 --> 37:16.567
It's weird and somewhat off-putting

37:16.651 --> 37:19.862
to be congratulated on doing nothing more
than accepting a note

37:19.946 --> 37:23.157
and having an ass pocket 
for someone to stick their hand into,

37:23.241 --> 37:25.618
but I guess
that's where my life has taken me.

37:29.372 --> 37:31.415
The Kavinsky thing is insane!

37:31.499 --> 37:35.503
Who knew you had a secret boner
for the king of the cafeteria crowd?

37:36.087 --> 37:38.464
I know, I'm just as shocked as you are.

37:38.547 --> 37:39.548
Did Margot freak?

37:40.132 --> 37:42.969
Actually, you know,
I've been avoiding her calls

37:43.052 --> 37:45.554
so she doesn't know yet.

37:47.348 --> 37:49.475
Hi, Margot. How's college?

37:49.934 --> 37:52.895
So listen, did I mention
I have a fake boyfriend?

37:54.230 --> 37:56.607
No? Yeah, it's Peter Kavinsky.

37:57.024 --> 37:58.234
How did it start?

37:58.317 --> 38:03.489
See, that's a funny story,
because it definitely was not because

38:03.572 --> 38:08.077
I was trying to convince your ex-boyfriend
that I wasn't in love with him,

38:08.160 --> 38:09.287
that's for sure.

38:09.370 --> 38:11.122
Oh, shit...

38:12.331 --> 38:14.625
[Skype ringtone beeps]

38:15.251 --> 38:16.168
Hi!

38:16.252 --> 38:21.340
Hi, finally. I feel like we haven't talked
in forever, so tell me everything.

38:21.632 --> 38:22.675
Well...

38:23.050 --> 38:26.846
I'm just making cupcakes tonight
for Kitty's bake sale.

38:26.929 --> 38:30.850
Cupcakes? No.
It's so much easier to do brownies.

38:30.933 --> 38:34.186
Well, I bought all the ingredients
for cupcakes,

38:34.270 --> 38:36.105
and you're not really here, so...

38:36.355 --> 38:39.358
Okay, fine, do cupcakes.
I'm sure they'll be great.

38:40.443 --> 38:43.321
So have you seen Josh at all lately?

38:43.696 --> 38:46.073
What? No. Why would I be seeing Josh?

38:46.532 --> 38:50.953
I don't know, 'cause he's our neighbor?
Is everything okay with you?

38:51.537 --> 38:54.248
No, you know... No, you know, sorry.

38:54.332 --> 38:57.043
I am just so excited
to get to these cupcakes.

38:57.126 --> 39:00.921
I think I'm gonna go and do that,
but it was so good to see you.

39:01.005 --> 39:02.381
-Wait, Lara Jean!
-Bye!

39:09.347 --> 39:10.598
[knock at door]

39:16.312 --> 39:17.313
Hey.

39:17.688 --> 39:20.816
Who are you supposed to be,
the Pillsbury Doughboy?

39:20.900 --> 39:23.652
No, I'm making cupcakes
for Kitty's bake sale.

39:24.779 --> 39:25.780
Can I come in?

39:26.822 --> 39:27.823
-Sure.
-Cool.

39:28.324 --> 39:33.412
You know it's easier if you make something
